@startuml
title Devils Resting - Message Lifecycle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam nodesep 45
skinparam ranksep 55
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam ArrowColor #687385
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.1
skinparam state {
  BorderColor #9fb0c7
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  FontColor #1f2937
}
skinparam note {
  BorderColor #d7dee8
  BackgroundColor #fbfcfe
  FontColor #445066
}

[*] --> NoDraft

NoDraft --> Drafting : focus composer
Drafting --> FilesQueued : attach files
FilesQueued --> Uploading : uploadAttachments
Uploading --> FilesQueued : cancel or partial failure
Uploading --> ReadyToSend : upload ids complete

Drafting --> Sending : send text only
ReadyToSend --> Sending : send text + upload ids

Sending : ws chat_message\nor attachment finalize
Sending --> Published : message persisted\nattachments linked
Sending --> Rejected : validation / permission /\nrate limit / slow mode
Rejected --> Drafting : edit and retry

Published --> Edited : edit_message
Edited --> Published : edit broadcast applied

Published --> ReadTracked : mark_read / read_receipt
Edited --> ReadTracked : later read receipts

Published --> Deleted : delete_message
Edited --> Deleted : delete_message
ReadTracked --> Edited : later edit
ReadTracked --> Deleted : later delete

Deleted --> [*]

note right of Published
A published message can also receive
reactions, pins and inbox notifications
without changing its core lifecycle state.
end note
@enduml
